{
  "stem": "15768.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And of course, he was always at my side when I was sick.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I happen to have had diphtheria and was very, very sick.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And he was at my bedside day and night looking after me through those first crucial hours when you have the high fever and when you're very, very sick.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So it was very comforting to know that, ultimately, no matter what I did, [LAUGHS] he would always be there to take care of me.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I did give him some hard times.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I-- When was the first time that you noticed that there was any wave of anti-Semitism?",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My family undoubtedly noticed early on.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My friends and my activities-- I don't really-- I can't really say that before 1938 and Kristallnacht, that I was subjected to any overt expressions of anti-Semitism.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I know that my older cousins told me later on, many years later, that they had confrontations in the schoolyard as early as 1935.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But essentially, it was a quiet town, and I really was not aware of any overt expressions of anti-Semitism.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I don't ever even recall being called a dirty Jew, which is something that was quite common then. 1938, Kristallnacht was of course the turning point when neighbors turned away and didn't speak to us.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "My father was arrested.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We had a cleaning lady for many, many years-- a lovely, lovely woman-- a good Christian who tried to prevent the-- the German, the SA, from-- as they were called-- arresting my father.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "To no avail, he was taken away.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Do you remember the date of that?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "That was November 9, 1938.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And he was taken away.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was at home.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We were sitting at the dinner table.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
